SIMPLE: marketable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marketable
<hw>Mar"ket*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fit
to be offered for sale in a market; such as may be justly and lawfully
sold; <as>as, decayed provisions are not
<ex>marketable</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Current in market; <as>as, <ex>marketable</ex>
value</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Wanted by purchasers; salable; <as>as, furs are not
<ex>marketable</ex> in that country</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marketableness</ent>⟦br⟧
